    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*harva-</w></mentioned>, ср.
            <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/><w>ar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>har</w><gloss><q>каждый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>har</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>harva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>haurva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>sárva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><lang/><w>όλος</w><gloss><q>весь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>каждый</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Переход %ir%i в %il%i
        объясняется влиянием последующего %iу%i | %ii%i, в котором опознается окончание родительного
        падежа; ср. элемент %ial%i в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_alḱī"/>. Связь с германской
        группой —- <mentioned xml:lang="got"
            ><lang/><w>alls</w><gloss><q>весь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="got"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>всякий</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><lang/><w>all</w></mentioned> и пр. — мало вероятна.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 89</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>55</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
            ><lang/><w>*harva-</w></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
            ><lang/><w>ar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><lang/><w>har</w><gloss><q>every</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>har</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>harva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>haurva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>sárva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><lang/><w>όλος</w><gloss><q>all</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>every</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The transition %ir%i to
        %il%i is explained by the influence of the following %iу%i | %ii%i, which is a genitive case
        ending; cf. element %ial%i in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_alḱī"/>. The connection with
        Germaninc languages —- <mentioned xml:lang="got"
            ><lang/><w>alls</w><gloss><q>all</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="got"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>every</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><lang/><w>all</w></mentioned> etc. — is highly doubtful.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 89</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>55</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
